### Phase 9: Push to Remote (After Human Approval)

#### Step 13: Push to Remote Repository

Only after approval:
```
#!/bin/bash
# scripts/13-push-to-remote.sh

set -e

source rebrand-config.env

echo "ğŸš€ Phase 9: Pushing to remote repository..."

# Check for approval
if [ ! -f "REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md" ]; then
    echo "âŒ Error: Review checklist not found"
    echo "Run ./scripts/12-generate-review-checklist.sh first"
    exit 1
fi

# Verify approval (basic check)
if ! grep -q "APPROVED - Safe to push" REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md; then
    echo "âŒ Error: Human approval not found in REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md"
    echo ""
    echo "Please complete the review checklist and mark as APPROVED"
    echo "before pushing to remote repository."
    exit 1
fi

echo "âœ… Human approval verified"
echo ""

# Confirm with user
read -p "Push to ${NEW_REPO_URL}? (yes/no): " CONFIRM
if [ "$CONFIRM" != "yes" ]; then
    echo "Push cancelled"
    exit 0
fi

# Push to remote
cd "$PROJECT_DIR"

echo "Pushing to remote..."
git push -u origin main

echo "âœ… Successfully pushed to ${NEW_REPO_URL}"
echo ""
echo "Repository URL: ${NEW_REPO_URL}"

cd ..
```

### Phase 10: Enable Post-Publication Monitoring

#### Step 14: Configure Security Monitoring

Enable ongoing security:
```
#!/bin/bash
# scripts/14-enable-monitoring.sh

set -e

source rebrand-config.env

echo "ğŸ“Š Phase 10: Enabling post-publication monitoring..."

cd "$PROJECT_DIR"

# Create Dependabot configuration
echo "Configuring Dependabot..."
mkdir -p .github
cat > .github/dependabot.yml << 'EOL'
version: 2
updates:
  - package-ecosystem: "npm"
    directory: "/"
    schedule:
      interval: "daily"
    open-pull-requests-limit: 10
    reviewers:
      - "stackconsult"
    labels:
      - "dependencies"
      - "security"
EOL

# Create security policy
echo "Creating security policy..."
cat > SECURITY.md << 'EOL'
# Security Policy

## Supported Versions

| Version | Supported          |
| ------- | ------------------ |
| 1.x.x   | :white_check_mark: |

## Reporting a Vulnerability

Please report security vulnerabilities by:
1. Opening a private security advisory
2. Emailing security contact (if configured)
3. DO NOT open public issues for security vulnerabilities

## Security Monitoring

This repository has:
- âœ… Dependabot enabled for automated dependency updates
- âœ… GitHub Security Advisories enabled
- âœ… Code scanning enabled (if applicable)

## Update Policy

Security updates are applied:
- Critical: Within 24 hours
- High: Within 1 week
- Medium: Within 1 month
- Low: Next scheduled update

## Security Practices

All code in this repository:
- âœ… Scanned for secrets before commit
- âœ… Scanned for malware
- âœ… Dependencies regularly audited
- âœ… Static code analysis performed
EOL

# Commit security configuration
git add .github/dependabot.yml SECURITY.md
git commit -m "chore: enable security monitoring

- Add Dependabot configuration
- Create security policy
- Enable automated vulnerability scanning"

git push origin main

# Enable GitHub security features via CLI
echo "Enabling GitHub security features..."
gh repo edit --enable-issues --enable-vulnerability-alerts

echo "âœ… Security monitoring enabled"
echo ""
echo "Monitor security at:"
echo "  ${NEW_REPO_URL}/security"

cd ..
```

